years. No one knows that better than me.

78
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:26,540
- You're gonna be OK.
- I am?

79
00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:28,540
Yes. I promise you.

80
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:32,260
The simple fact that we can
talk about this together is a good sign.

81
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:34,540
- A good sign?
- Yeah.

82
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:36,180
How could it be a good sign?

83
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:41,420
Because crazy people don't sit around
wondering if they're nuts.

84
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:44,100
- They don't?
- No. They've got better things to do.

85
00:05:44,140 --> 00:05:45,660
Take it from me.

86
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:50,940
A very good sign that you're crazy is an
inability to ask the question, "Am I crazy?"

87
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:54,180
Even if the answer is yes?

88
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:56,220
Crazy people don't ask, you see?

89
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:58,460
Huh.

90
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:01,860
What do you say? Let's call it a night.
You can go up and get some sleep.

91
00:06:01,940 --> 00:06:03,940
- Then in the morning...
- Wait.

92
00:06:03,980 --> 00:06:06,460
- What's the matter?
- It doesn't make sense.

93
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:08,660
- Sure it does.
- No.

94
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:11,740
- Where's the problem?
- The problem is...

95
00:06:11,820 --> 00:06:14,260
- You are crazy.
- So?

96
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:18,580
So you said a crazy person
would never admit that.

97
00:06:19,180 --> 00:06:21,460
Ah. I see.

98
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:24,300
So?

99
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:28,220
- It's a point.
- So how can you admit it?

100
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:31,020
Well, because...

101
00:06:32,580 --> 00:06:35,620
I'm also dead.

102
00:06:35,660 --> 00:06:37,900
Aren't I?

103
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:45,100
- You died a week ago.
- Aneurysm. 63 years old.

104
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:47,860
The funeral's tomorrow.

105
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:02,700
Sorry.

106
00:07:02,780 --> 00:07:06,180
- Did I... Did I hurt you?
- No. It's OK.

107
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:07,180
Good.

108
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:10,180
Mr. Dobbs, you gonna stand there forever?

109
00:07:10,260 --> 00:07:12,260
This is my daughter Catherine.

110
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:14,020
- Hi.
- Hi.

111
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:16,300
Mr. Dobbs is in our infinite program.

112
